<subSubSection id="C3446556E354FFA6FF6BBB23FD1599E5" pageId="1" pageNumber="586" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BE136DDE354FFA6FF6BBB23FD1599E5" blockId="1.[151,1437,1105,2029]" pageId="1" pageNumber="586">
<emphasis id="B92AEACFE354FFA6FF6BBB23FECC99D9" bold="true" box="[201,336,1141,1165]" pageId="1" pageNumber="586">Etymology.</emphasis>
The generic name is derived from Latin word “ 
<emphasis id="B92AEACFE354FFA6FCC9BB23FC5299D9" box="[875,974,1141,1165]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="586">luculent-</emphasis>
”, meaning “ 
<emphasis id="B92AEACFE354FFA6FBFFBB23FB5099D9" box="[1117,1228,1141,1165]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="586">luciferous</emphasis>
” and “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E4D5EE354FFA6FABFBB23FAC099D9" box="[1309,1372,1141,1165]" class="Insecta" family="Saldidae" genus="Salda" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="586" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B92AEACFE354FFA6FABFBB23FAC099D9" box="[1309,1372,1141,1165]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="586">Salda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” (the 
<typeStatus id="54E5887FE354FFA6FF35BBCCFF5B99E6" box="[151,199,1178,1202]" pageId="1" pageNumber="586">type</typeStatus>
genus of this family). Gender feminine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3446556E354FFA6FF6BBBEBFE289981" box="[201,436,1213,1238]" pageId="1" pageNumber="586" type="distribution">
